commit.message: Fix incorrect Podcasts download location
Minor markup corrections
Remove references to Music menu item; SoundJuicer not needed anymore
I fail to find any UI for smart playlists, hence comment section
I fail to remove a static playlist, hence comment section
Remove references to View menu item
Replace various HTTP by HTTPS links
Remove references to Edit menu item in most cases (except for playlists section)
Update podcast screenshot for Rhythmbox 3.4
Update notification area page for Rhythmbox 3.4
Update internet radio screenshot for Rhythmbox 3.4
Update steps in library-filter-browser
Update steps how to import tracks
Update how to start Rhythmbox 3.4 in times of GNOME 3
Remove a stray tag. (Docbook, sigh.)
Remove references to non-existing 'Edit' menu item
Remove references to non-existing 'Music' menu item
Remove references to non-existing 'Control' menu item
Update numerous screenshots for Rhythmbox 3.4
Remove 'Minimized Window' section - not existing in Rhythmbox 3.4
Update text and screenshot of 'App window' page for Rhythmbox 3.4
Fix typo in help
Update Brazilian Portuguese translation

query-creator: check sort index on num_sort_options, not num_property_options

https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=791815
Update Esperanto translation
Update Turkish translation
Updated Spanish translation
Update Indonesian translation
rhythmdb: allow mountpoint property to be set to NULL
Update Slovak translation

issue_comments.body:
The FAQ says that merge requests from GitHub will not be accepted...
- https://wiki.gnome.org/Sysadmin/GitHub

You probably should file a bug report on bugzilla with the patch included.

Hope this helps.

unless there has been a recent change, PRs need to be done via gnome bugzilla - not via GitHub

https://bugzilla.gnome.org/enter_bug.cgi

Please don't mind that I do no want to create an account and write a bug 
report for this little finding ;)

On 29.08.2016 08:12, David Mohammed wrote:

> unless there has been a recent change, PRs need to be done via gnome 
> bugzilla - not via GitHub
> 
> https://bugzilla.gnome.org/enter_bug.cgi
> 
> —
> You are receiving this because you authored the thread.
> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub 
> https://github.com/GNOME/rhythmbox/pull/2#issuecomment-243039993, or 
> mute the thread 
> https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/ABZ-age-sUluVBHtdPY4o4VyN41aZq_rks5qkng3gaJpZM4JuCuy.

Thank you for contributing to rhythmbox!

rhythmbox uses Bugzilla for code review.

If you have never contributed to GNOME before make sure you have read the
getting started documentation:
http://www.gnome.org/get-involved

Otherwise please visit
https://wiki.gnome.org/Newcomers/CodeContributionWorkflow
and follow the instructions there to upload your change to Bugzilla.
Closed as no PRs are accepted here...
